The morning wakes with silver light,
A gentle hush after the night.
Dewdrops cling to blades of green,
Like fragile dreams not fully seen.
A distant bird begins its song,
Reminding hearts where they belong.
Clouds drift slow in painted skies,
Mirroring thoughts that softly rise.
And in this calm, so deep, so true,
The world feels freshly born anew.
